The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Bengal | Briefs
                                                                                                                     4                                                                                      BRIEFS
                  
	Calcutta, Nov. 20: Two police officers were injured when a mob, allegedly led by Trinamul supporters, hurled bombs at them during a raid in Rajarhats Sashan.     
	The mob damaged two police vehicles and tried to snatch a murder accused the cops had taken along with them. Shyamal Sarkar and Manirul Islam Sarkar suffered splinter injuries.        
	Calcutta: A speeding truck smashed the head of a man who had got stuck in the divider railings on Central Avenue while trying to squeeze through a gap between the rods. Bappa Pal, 27, was an Assam resident.         
	Calcutta: A youth duped an elderly man out of Rs 2.5 lakh with the bait of a dollar for every Rs 20. Jodhpur Park resident Ashish Kumar Ghosh, 72, later found that the bag of dollars the conman had given him had only newspapers stuffed inside.        
	Darjeeling: A 19-year-old Chinese tourist has filed a police complaint alleging a youth had tried to molest her on Darjeelings Nehru Road on Friday evening.         
	Midnapore: Maoists allegedly abducted a teacher and a woman worker involved with the Integrated Child Development Scheme in West Midnapore on Friday.        
	Calcutta: The state government on Saturday cleared the 16.72km Joka-BBD Bag Metro Rail project.                                                                                                                                                       
